Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

structural state definitions
dependency-aware activation model
tetherless settlement logic
a minimal executable reference demonstration
outputs and reference traces

STINT-Money defines a deterministic structural model where financial correctness is preserved independently of continuous network connectivity:

resolve(structure) ->
    RESOLVED   if complete and consistent
    ABSTAIN    if insufficient structure
    CONFLICT   if inconsistent structure

Activation is modeled separately:

activate(structure, dependencies) ->
    READY
    BLOCKED
    RELEASED
    FROZEN


What This Demonstrates

• financial correctness without continuous network connectivity
• independence from synchronization and ordered communication
• deterministic convergence under delay and unordered availability
• separation of truth and activation
• dependency-aware activation control
• structural maturity governing correctness
• safe handling of incomplete or conflicting structure
• reproducible canonical outcomes across independent systems


Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

structure-based correctness
independence from continuous connectivity as a requirement
order-independent merge behavior
deterministic convergence under delayed availability
separation of resolution and activation
dependency-aware activation control
reproducibility under equivalent structure
explicit handling of insufficient and conflicting structure

Conformance is judged by observable behavior, not internal implementation.


Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

STINT-Money is part of the broader Shunyaya framework.

It builds on:

SLANG → structural resolution without execution
ORL → structural correctness without ordering
STIME → structural time (time without clocks)
SSUM-Time → structural time reconstruction
STOCRS → structure-first computation

STINT extends this progression by removing continuous network dependency as a requirement for correctness.


